<section id="petra">
<h2>Petra</h2>
<img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/e/e5/Petra_Jordan_BW_21.JPG" alt="Petra">
<p>Petra is Jordan’s most famous archaeological site, known as the Rose City. It’s a UNESCO World Heritage Site.</p>
<h3>Facts:</h3>
<ul>
<li>Located in southern Jordan</li>
<li>Best time to visit: Spring & Autumn</li>
<li>Entry Fee: $70</li>
</ul>
<table>
<tr>
<th>Feature</th>
<th>Details</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Main Attraction</td>
<td>The Treasury</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Built</td>
<td>c. 5th century BC</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Visitors</td>
<td>Over 1 million annually</td>
</tr>
</table>
</section>

<section id="wadi_rum">
<h2>Wadi Rum</h2>
<img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/2/21/Wadi_Rum_sunset.jpg" alt="Wadi Rum">
<p>Wadi Rum, also known as the Valley of the Moon, is a protected desert wilderness with dramatic sandstone mountains.</p>
<h3>Activities:</h3>
<ol>
<li>Jeep Tours</li>
<li>Camping under stars</li>
<li>Hiking and rock climbing</li>
<li>Hot air balloon rides</li>
</ol>
</section>

<section id="dead_sea">
<h2>Dead Sea</h2>
<img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/4/48/Dead_Sea_Aerial_View.jpg" alt="Dead Sea">
<p>The Dead Sea is the lowest point on Earth, famous for its salty water and mineral-rich mud.</p>
<ul>
<li>Float effortlessly due to high salt content</li>
<li>Health resorts and spa treatments</li>
<li>All year round visits</li>
</ul>
</section>

<section id="jerash">
<h2>Jerash</h2>
<img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/d/d3/Jerash_Forum.JPG" alt="Jerash">
<p>Jerash is known for its well-preserved Roman ruins including theaters, temples, and colonnaded streets.</p>
<h3>Highlights:</h3>
<ol>
<li>Oval Forum</li>
<li>Hadrian’s Arch</li>
<li>Hippodrome</li>
<li>South Theater</li>
</ol>
</section>

